{"type":"text","timestamp":1775859858406,"sessionID":"ses_28682179cffeQIDOZszRsQlgpm","part":{"id":"prt_d797ed49d001Cr1qFLMXS70lyt","messageID":"msg_d797ecacc001Cnn1X70KBXhE70","sessionID":"ses_28682179cffeQIDOZszRsQlgpm","type":"text","text":"## AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Archive Summary\n\n### ✅ Completed\n\n**Core Implementation (Phase 1-6):**\n- `picod.go`: PicoD struct, New() constructor, functional options (WithWorkDir, WithLimits, WithSecurityOpts, WithLogger), Run(), Start(), RunWithStreaming()\n- `executor.go`: Command/CommandResult structs, Executor with Run() and Start() methods, limitedBuffer for output capture\n- `limits.go`: ResourceLimits struct with Validate() and Apply(), DefaultResourceLimits()\n- `security.go`: SecurityOptions struct with Validate(), ValidateCommand(), IsPathSafe(), DropPrivileges()\n- `output.go`: OutputHandler interface, RunWithStreaming() with teeWriter for streaming output\n- `process.go`: Process struct with Wait(), Kill(), Signal(), KillTree() methods\n- `errors.go`: ExecutionError type with 6 error types (Timeout, OOM, Cancelled, Security, Resource, Exec)\n- `config.go`: Config struct and LoadConfig() from environment variables\n\n**Tests (9 test files):**\n- All core types have corresponding `*_test.go` files\n- Unit tests for config, errors, executor, limits, output, picod, process, security\n- Integration tests for lifecycle, concurrency, resource limits, streaming, signal handling\n\n**Documentation:**\n- `design.md`: Complete architecture design (684 lines)\n- `tasks.md`: Detailed task breakdown (260 lines)\n\n### ⏸️ Deferred / Incomplete\n\n**From tasks.md (all tasks marked as `[ ]` pending):**\n- TASK-031: CPU limit enforcement via cgroups (Linux-specific)\n- TASK-042: DropPrivileges() implementation exists but not fully integrated\n- Full integration of CPU limits in Apply() method\n\n**Test Failures (need fixes):**\n- `TestExecutor_Run_Success`: Output capture issue\n- `TestExecutor_Run_WithStdout`: stdout buffer assertion mismatch  \n- `TestLimitedBuffer_ExceedsLimit`: Buffer limit handling bug\n- `TestExecutor_WithTimeout`: Timeout detection not setting Timeout=true flag\n- `TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle`: Missing `/usr/bin/echo` in test environment\n- `TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming`: Streaming test execution failure\n\n**Documentation:**\n- No godoc comments on exported types/functions (DOC-001, DOC-002, DOC-003)\n- No `pkg/picod/README.md` usage guide\n\n**Status:** Stage ST-3 (Implementation complete, tests need fixes, documentation pending)","time":{"start":1775859858403,"end":1775859858403}}}
